1. Is reviewer output-only review (reading committed code, not developer reasoning) sufficient for adversarial evaluation? Or does losing the reasoning trace degrade quality?
2. Does the beads/kanban contract hold up across autonomous agents, or will they drift?
3. Is the async iterate speed (minutes per round) acceptable for real-world tasks, or does it kill momentum?
4. Should the developer invoke harnesses as a tool (hybrid), or run raw with terminal/patch?
